Greater China Daybook: Hui Xian Debut; Taiwan Growth; Citic Bank Earnings

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-04-28T21:46:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-28/greater-china-daybook-hui-xian-debut-taiwan-growth-citic-bank-earnings.html
Hong Kong billionaire  Li Ka-shing ’s
Hui Xian Real Estate Investment Trust, the city’s first stock
sale denominated in yuan, will begin trading today after selling
units at the low end of a price range.  The trust raised 10.5 billion yuan ($1.6 billion) selling
units at 5.24 yuan each, according to a statement to the Hong
Kong stock exchange yesterday. The units fell to 5.18 yuan in
gray market trading, the locally based English-language Standard
newspaper said today, citing Phillip Securities.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net . 